laboratory_examinations.findings: Mild prominence of the extrahepatic biliary tree with maximum diameter of 13 mm. No upstream dilatation of the intrahepatic bile ducts. The common bile duct tapers gradually to the level of the ampulla without filling defect or extrinsic mass effect. The contour of the bile ducts is smooth, without areas of stenosis, irregularity, or thickening. The liver is normal in size and contour with normal parenchymal signal, without evidence of hepatic steatosis. No focal hepatic lesion is identified. The pancreas and pancreatic duct, spleen, right kidney, and adrenal glands are unremarkable. A 1.5 cm hemorrhagic cyst is noted in the left mid kidney. No lymphadenopathy or ascites. Mild atelectatic changes noted at each lung base.
